Reasoning: The paper discusses web content delivery and network security, which are closely related to the sub-category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses protective mechanisms and security models, which are related to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The empirical exploration of the relationship between web hosting infrastructure and RPKI deployment involves data analysis and statistical methods, which are related to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the challenges of protecting web hosting infrastructure, which are related to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the business reasons why operators are hesitant to deploy RPKI, which are related to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
